  m_Name: Metacarpals_L
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Metacarpals_L
  partName: Metacarpals Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - 'The left metacarpals form the central skeletal framework of the canine left
    forepaw and extend between the carpal bones and phalanges. These long bones support
    the digits while distributing weight and mechanical forces during movement. They
    contribute significantly to paw stability, balance, and coordinated '
  - locomotion by maintaining proper alignment of the forepaw during ground contact.
    Muscles and tendons attached to the metacarpals control digital motion and support
    efficient stride mechanics. The bones also help absorb impact forces generated
    during running and jumping activities.
